{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01ERkqyubWofZ5XkzzNHmq6k","type":"tool_result","content":"1\tpub mod agent;\n2\tpub mod cron;\n3\tpub mod health;\n4\tpub mod output;\n5\tpub mod repl;\n6\tpub mod sessions;\n7\tpub mod tui;\n8\t\n9\tuse clap::Subcommand;\n10\t\n11\t#[derive(Subcommand)]\n12\tpub enum Commands {\n13\t    /// Check service health\n14\t    Health,\n15\t    /// Manage sessions\n16\t    Sessions {\n17\t        #[command(subcommand)]\n18\t        action: sessions::Action,\n19\t    },\n20\t    /// Run a single agent turn\n21\t    Agent(agent::AgentArgs),\n22\t    /// Start an interactive chat session (REPL)\n23\t    Repl(repl::ReplArgs),\n24\t    /// Start the full-screen terminal UI (TUI)\n25\t    Tui(tui::TuiArgs),\n26\t    /// Manage scheduled agent jobs\n27\t    Cron {\n28\t        #[command(subcommand)]\n29\t        action: cron::Action,\n30\t    },\n31\t}\n32\t\n33\tpub async fn run(cmd: Commands) -> anyhow::Result<()> {\n34\t    match cmd {\n35\t        Commands::Health => health::run().await,\n36\t        Commands::Sessions { action } => sessions::run(action).await,\n37\t        Commands::Agent(args) => agent::run(args).await,\n38\t        Commands::Repl(args) => repl::run(args).await,\n39\t        Commands::Tui(args) => tui::run(args).await,\n40\t        Commands::Cron { action } => cron::run(action).await,\n41\t    }\n42\t}\n43\t\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01WZqWFGu49DUSvyMsDxFM7U","session_id":"b35f4001-d232-4171-b853-fb6a26d102e1","uuid":"72db76e9-4bc2-498a-a5f6-d0f5b7075502","timestamp":"2026-04-02T06:23:33.865Z"}
