{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WZqWFGu49DUSvyMsDxFM7U","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a final summary document:\n\n## Thorough Codebase Overview: Ratatui TUI & Platform Infrastructure\n\nBased on my exploration of `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode`, here's a comprehensive overview:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **.ralph-tui/ Directory Structure**\n\n**Location:** `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/.ralph-tui/`\n\n**Files:**\n- **config.toml** (210B): Ralph-tui orchestration config. Version 2.1, tracker: \"json\", agent: \"claude\", autoCommit: false\n- **session.json** (8.4K): Active session state. 48 total tasks with mixed \"completed\" and \"open\" status. Current active task: US-034 (Ratatui theming, accessibility, and fallback policy)\n- **session-meta.json** (387B): Session metadata with status \"running\"\n- **progress.md** (263B): Progress tracking document (minimal usage currently)\n- **ralph.lock** (218B): Lock file for session management\n- **iterations/** directory: Contains 47 iteration logs (US-000 through US-046), tracking individual task execution details\n\n**Key Insight:** This is an active Ralph-tui orchestration session running Claude agent on a PRD-based task list. Currently working on **US-034: Ratatui theming, accessibility, and fallback policy** (the theme/color work).\n\n---\n\n### 2. Ratatui-Related Code in Crates\n\n**Primary TUI Implementation:** `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/cli/src/cmd/tui.rs` (1,793 lines)\n\n**Key Components:**\n\n#### a. **Ratatui Dependencies** (from crates/cli/Cargo.toml)\n```\nratatui = \"0.28\"\ncrossterm = \"0.28\"\nunicode-segmentation = \"1.12\"\nunicode-width = \"0.2\"\n```\n\n#### b. **Core TUI Structures**\n\n| Struct | Purpose | Lines |\n|--------|---------|-------|\n| `AppState` | Main application state (default 297 lines) | Holds conversation, status, input buffer, worker panel, tool approval modal |\n| `InputBuffer` | Multi-line IME-safe text entry | Implements grapheme-aware cursor movement, supports CJK input |\n| `RuntimeState` | Flight state tracking | Tracks in-flight requests and session ID |\n| `ToolApprovalModal` | Tool approval UI widget | Displays tool name, params summary, risk level, selection state |\n| `AppAction` | Action enum | None, Submit, ToolApprovalResolved, StopSelectedTask, Quit |\n| `WorkerPanelState` | Multi-agent task monitor | Tracks 500 max tasks with virtual scrolling |\n| `DrawLimiter` | Frame rate limiter | 16ms interval throttling (60 FPS) |\n| `TerminalGuard` | RAII terminal cleanup | Drop impl restores terminal state on panic/exit |\n\n#### c. **Rendering Pipeline**\n\n**Main Render Function** (lines 139-210):\n```rust\nfn draw_ui(frame: &mut Frame<'_>, app: &AppState)\n```\n\nSplits screen into 4 panes (68/32% horizontal split):\n1. **Conversation Pane** (top-left): Scrollable conversation history with delta streaming\n2. **Worker Panel** (top-right):\n   - Worker Task List (virtual scrolled, 5+ rows minimum)\n   - Worker Details (6 rows fixed)\n3. **Status Pane** (bottom-left, 5 rows): Last 4 status messages with error categorization\n4. **Input Pane** (bottom-right, 3 rows): Multi-line text editor with cursor position tracking\n\n**Layout** (lines 212-223):\n- Uses `Layout::vertical` and `Layout::horizontal` with `Constraint::Min`, `Constraint::Length`, `Constraint::Percentage`\n- Modal dialog rendering with `centered_rect()` using 80% width, centered positioning\n\n#### d. **Styling** (Current Implementation)\n\n**Style Usage** (lines 143-147, repeated pattern):\n```rust\n.title_style(Style::default().add_modifier(Modifier::BOLD))\n```\n\n**Current Styling:**\n- Only BOLD modifiers used for pane titles\n- No color definitions\n- No background/foreground customization\n- No theme abstraction layer\n\n#### e. **Terminal Capability Handling**\n\n**Raw Mode & Alternate Screen** (lines 39-40):\n```rust\nenable_raw_mode()?;\nexecute!(io::stdout(), EnterAlternateScreen)?;\n```\n\n**Restoration** (lines 1465-1469):\n```rust\nfn restore_terminal() -> io::Result<()> {\n    disable_raw_mode()?;\n    execute!(io::stdout(), LeaveAlternateScreen)?;\n    Ok(())\n}\n```\n\n**Panic Hook** (lines 1471-1481):\n- Installs global panic handler via `std::sync::Once`\n- Ensures terminal restoration even on panic\n- Preserves original panic hook\n\n---\n\n### 3. Platform Crate Structure\n\n**Location:** `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/platform/src/`\n\n**Files:**\n- **lib.rs** (11 lines): Module exports for:\n  - `remote_trigger_dispatch_service`\n  - `security`\n  - `trigger_scheduler_service`\n\n- **security.rs** (100+ lines): Secret scanning & path validation\n  - `SecretScanner` trait\n  - `DefaultSecretScanner` with rules for: OpenAI, GitHub PAT, AWS access keys, private keys\n  - `PathValidationError` enum for secure file operations\n  - `ScanThenWritePolicy` for write-time validation\n\n- **trigger_scheduler_service.rs** (50+ lines): Local cron scheduling\n  - `TriggerSchedulerPolicy` for enable/disable controls\n  - `LocalTriggerSchedulerService` for durable task scheduling\n  - Integration with `TriggerTaskStateStore`\n\n- **remote_trigger_dispatch_service.rs**: Remote trigger orchestration\n- Test files for security, trigger dispatch, and scheduler\n\n**No UI/Display Logic:** Platform crate is infrastructure-focused (security, scheduling, remote dispatch)\n\n---\n\n### 4. Settings/Configuration Structures\n\n**Location:** `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/config/src/schema.rs`\n\n**Main Config Struct:**\n```rust\npub struct Config {\n    pub providers: ProvidersConfig,\n    pub routing: RoutingConfig,\n    pub mcp: McpConfig,\n    pub sandbox: Option<SandboxConfig>,\n    pub memory: Option<MemoryConfig>,\n    pub context: ContextConfig,\n    pub remote_runtime: RemoteRuntimeConfig,\n}\n```\n\n**Provider Configs:**\n- `OpenRouterConfig`, `ZhipuConfig`, `OpenAiConfig`, `AnthropicConfig`, `LlamaCppConfig`\n\n**Context Management:**\n- `compress_chars_threshold`: 600k chars default\n- `keep_recent_messages`: 8 default\n- `tool_result_max_chars`: 40k default\n\n**No Theme Config:** Settings schema has no color/theme fields yet\n\n---\n\n### 5. Color/Theme-Related Code\n\n**Existing Color/Theme Code:** Minimal\n\n**In output.rs** (701 lines):\n- `ErrorCategory` enum (5 variants): Policy, Auth, Transport, State, Validation\n- `ToolRiskLevel` enum (3 variants): Low, Medium, High\n- Classification functions but NO color mapping\n\n**Example:**\n```rust\npub fn error_category_label(category: ErrorCategory) -> &'static str {\n    match category {\n        ErrorCategory::Policy => \"policy\",\n        ErrorCategory::Auth => \"auth\",\n        // ...\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**In tui.rs:**\n- No color constants\n- No theme struct\n- No palette definitions\n- Only `Style::default()` with optional `add_modifier(Modifier::BOLD)`\n\n---\n\n### 6. Terminal Capability Detection Code\n\n**Current Implementation:** None\n\n**What Exists:**\n- Direct use of `CrosstermBackend::new(io::stdout())`\n- No terminal capability probing\n- Assumes full ratatui/crossterm support\n- No fallback to basic ASCII/ANSI mode\n\n**Missing:**\n- No `terminfo` parsing\n- No color depth detection (truecolor vs 256 vs 16)\n- No width/height minimum validation\n- No feature detection for mouse, unicode, etc.\n\n---\n\n### 7. Key Files to Reference\n\n| File | Lines | Purpose |\n|------|-------|---------|\n| `/crates/cli/src/cmd/tui.rs` | 1,793 | Main TUI loop, rendering, input handling |\n| `/crates/cli/src/cmd/output.rs` | 701 | Error classification, tool risk, stream formatting |\n| `/crates/cli/Cargo.toml` | 26 | Dependencies including ratatui 0.28, crossterm 0.28 |\n| `/crates/config/src/schema.rs` | 150+ | Configuration structures (no theme fields) |\n| `/crates/platform/src/security.rs` | 100+ | Secret scanning & path validation |\n| `/.ralph-tui/session.json` | - | Active task tracker (US-034 is active) |\n\n---\n\n### 8. Architecture Notes\n\n**Multi-Agent Worker Monitoring:**\n- `WorkerPanelState` tracks up to 500 tasks\n- Virtual scrolling with selection state\n- Task details: `task_id`, `status`, `summary`, `started_at`, `updated_at`\n\n**Event-Driven Streaming:**\n- Unbounded MPSC channel for UI events\n- `UiEvent` enum for: delta, tool start/done, approval, worker status\n- Broadcast channel for worker monitor events\n\n**Input Handling:**\n- Grapheme-aware text manipulation (unicode-segmentation)\n- IME preedit support\n- History with up/down navigation (100 item limit)\n- Multi-line support with Shift+Enter\n\n**Error Classification:**\n- Transport (timeout, connection, DNS)\n- Auth (401, 403, API key)\n- Policy (permission denied, forbidden)\n- Validation (invalid, parse error)\n- State (not found, invalid state)\n\n---\n\n### 9. Current State Summary\n\n**Completed (US-029 to US-033):**\n- Ratatui foundation integrated\n- Streaming renderer\n- Input editing with IME support\n- Tool approval modal\n- Worker/task monitor\n- Multi-pane layout with virtual scrolling\n\n**In Progress (US-034):**\n- **Ratatui theming, accessibility, and fallback policy** ← Currently active task\n- This covers: color themes, accessibility features, terminal capability fallbacks\n\n**Open Tasks (US-035+):**\n- Acceptance test suites (LLM compat, bridge mode, MCP, KAIROS, multi-agent, etc.)\n- Architecture validation\n\n---\n\nThis is a mature, feature-rich TUI with comprehensive input handling and multi-agent task orchestration, but minimal styling/theming infrastructure currently. The active task (US-034) is specifically for implementing the theme layer."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b35f4001-d232-4171-b853-fb6a26d102e1","uuid":"d8a96b1c-5833-44c3-b628-bcab35bbb9fd","timestamp":"2026-04-02T06:24:05.832Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase at /