{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VTk9aQggxMqJpMwyH5QxEf","type":"tool_result","content":"1399\t\n1400\tfn spawn_task_stop(\n1401\t    bootstrap_state: Arc<BootstrapState>,\n1402\t    task_id: String,\n1403\t    ui_tx: tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedSender<UiEvent>,\n1404\t) {\n1405\t    tokio::spawn(async move {\n1406\t        let registry = Arc::clone(&bootstrap_state.tool_registry);\n1407\t        let tool_ctx = Arc::new(bootstrap_state.tool_ctx());\n1408\t        let args = serde_json::json!({\n1409\t            \"task_id\": task_id.clone(),\n1410\t            \"summary\": \"stopped from tui worker panel\"\n1411\t        });\n1412\t\n1413\t        let _ = ui_tx.send(UiEvent::ToolStart {\n1414\t            name: \"task_stop\".to_string(),\n1415\t            args: args.clone(),\n1416\t        });\n1417\t\n1418\t        let result = registry\n1419\t            .execute(\"task_stop\", args, &tool_ctx)\n1420\t            .await\n1421\t            .map_err(|err| err.to_string());\n1422\t\n1423\t        if let Ok(payload) = &result\n1424\t            && let Ok(value) = serde_json::from_str::<Value>(payload)\n1425\t            && let (Some(task_id), Some(status_raw)) = (\n1426\t                value.get(\"task_id\").and_then(Value::as_str),\n1427\t                value.get(\"status\").and_then(Value::as_str),\n1428\t            )\n1429\t            && let Some(status) = worker_status_label(status_raw)\n1430\t        {\n1431\t            let summary = value\n1432\t                .get(\"summary\")\n1433\t                .and_then(Value::as_str)\n1434\t                .map(ToString::to_string);\n1435\t            let _ = ui_tx.send(UiEvent::WorkerStatus {\n1436\t                task_id: task_id.to_string(),\n1437\t                status: status.to_string(),\n1438\t                summary,\n1439\t                timestamp: SystemTime::now(),\n1440\t            });\n1441\t        }\n1442\t\n1443\t        let _ = ui_tx.send(UiEvent::ToolDone {\n1444\t            name: \"task_stop\".to_string(),\n1445\t            success: result.is_ok(),\n1446\t        });\n1447\t\n1448\t        if let Err(message) = result {\n1449\t            let _ = ui_tx.send(UiEvent::ToolError {\n1450\t                name: \"task_stop\".to_string(),\n1451\t                message,\n1452\t            });\n1453\t        }\n1454\t    });\n1455\t}\n1456\t\n1457\tstruct TerminalGuard;\n1458\t\n1459\timpl Drop for TerminalGuard {\n1460\t    fn drop(&mut self) {\n1461\t        let _ = restore_terminal();\n1462\t    }\n1463\t}\n1464\t\n1465\tfn restore_terminal() -> io::Result<()> {\n1466\t    disable_raw_mode()?;\n1467\t    execute!(io::stdout(), LeaveAlternateScreen)?;\n1468\t    Ok(())\n1469\t}\n1470\t\n1471\tfn install_panic_restoration_hook() {\n1472\t    static INIT_HOOK: std::sync::Once = std::sync::Once::new();\n1473\t\n1474\t    INIT_HOOK.call_once(|| {\n1475\t        let original = std::panic::take_hook();\n1476\t        std::panic::set_hook(Box::new(move |panic_info| {\n1477\t            let _ = restore_terminal();\n1478\t            original(panic_info);\n1479\t        }));\n1480\t    });\n1481\t}\n1482\t\n1483\t#[cfg(test)]\n1484\tmod tests {\n1485\t    use super::{\n1486\t        AppAction, AppState, ConversationLine, DrawLimiter, StatusKind, ToolApprovalAction,\n1487\t        WorkerUiEvent, split_layout,\n1488\t    };\n1489\t    use crossterm::event::{KeyCode, KeyEvent, KeyEventKind, KeyEventState, KeyModifiers};\n1490\t    use ratatui::layout::Rect;\n1491\t    use serde_json::json;\n1492\t    use std::time::{Duration, Instant};\n1493\t\n1494\t    #[test]\n1495\t    fn splits_into_four_panes() {\n1496\t        let [conversation, worker, status, input] = split_layout(Rect::new(0, 0, 120, 40));\n1497\t\n1498\t        assert_eq!(conversation.width + worker.width, 120);\n1499\t        assert_eq!(status.height, 5);\n1500\t        assert_eq!(input.height, 3);\n1501\t    }\n1502\t\n1503\t    #[test]\n1504\t    fn ctrl_c_quits() {\n1505\t        let mut app = AppState::default();\n1506\t\n1507\t        let action = app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Char('c'), KeyModifiers::CONTROL));\n1508\t\n1509\t        assert!(matches!(action, AppAction::Quit));\n1510\t    }\n1511\t\n1512\t    #[test]\n1513\t    fn appends_deltas_to_active_assistant_message() {\n1514\t        let mut app = AppState::default();\n1515\t        app.apply_delta(\"hello\");\n1516\t        app.apply_delta(\" world\");\n1517\t        app.close_active_assistant();\n1518\t        app.apply_delta(\"new\");\n1519\t\n1520\t        assert_eq!(app.conversation.len(), 2);\n1521\t        match &app.conversation[0] {\n1522\t            ConversationLine::Assistant(content) => assert_eq!(content, \"hello world\"),\n1523\t            other => panic!(\"unexpected conversation entry: {other:?}\"),\n1524\t        }\n1525\t        match &app.conversation[1] {\n1526\t            ConversationLine::Assistant(content) => assert_eq!(content, \"new\"),\n1527\t            other => panic!(\"unexpected conversation entry: {other:?}\"),\n1528\t        }\n1529\t    }\n1530\t\n1531\t    #[test]\n1532\t    fn tool_timeline_marks_success_and_failure() {\n1533\t        let mut app = AppState::default();\n1534\t        app.push_tool_done(\"shell\".to_string(), true);\n1535\t        app.push_tool_done(\"shell\".to_string(), false);\n1536\t\n1537\t        let lines = app.render_conversation();\n1538\t        assert!(lines.iter().any(|l| l.to_string().contains(\"[ok]\")));\n1539\t        assert!(lines.iter().any(|l| l.to_string().contains(\"[fail]\")));\n1540\t    }\n1541\t\n1542\t    #[test]\n1543\t    fn conversation_scroll_navigation_changes_offset() {\n1544\t        let mut app = AppState::default();\n1545\t        app.conversation_scroll = 10;\n1546\t        let _ = app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Up, KeyModifiers::CONTROL));\n1547\t        assert_eq!(app.conversation_scroll, 9);\n1548\t        let _ = app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::PageDown, KeyModifiers::NONE));\n1549\t        assert_eq!(app.conversation_scroll, 19);\n1550\t    }\n1551\t\n1552\t    #[test]\n1553\t    fn grapheme_aware_backspace_and_cursor_navigation() {\n1554\t        let mut app = AppState::default();\n1555\t        let _ = app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Char('a'), KeyModifiers::NONE));\n1556\t        let _ = app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Char('🙂'), KeyModifiers::NONE));\n1557\t        let _ = app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Char('你'), KeyModifiers::NONE));\n1558\t\n1559\t        let _ = app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Left, KeyModifiers::NONE));\n1560\t        let _ = app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Backspace, KeyModifiers::NONE));\n1561\t\n1562\t        assert_eq!(app.input.as_str(), \"a你\");\n1563\t        let _ = app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Right, KeyModifiers::NONE));\n1564\t        assert_eq!(app.input.as_str(), \"a你\");\n1565\t    }\n1566\t\n1567\t    #[test]\n1568\t    fn up_down_recalls_input_history() {\n1569\t        let mut app = AppState::default();\n1570\t        app.input.set_text(\"first\".to_string());\n1571\t        assert!(matches!(app.submit_input(), AppAction::Submit(_)));\n1572\t        app.input.set_text(\"second\".to_string());\n1573\t        assert!(matches!(app.submit_input(), AppAction::Submit(_)));\n1574\t\n1575\t        let _ = app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Up, KeyModifiers::NONE));\n1576\t        assert_eq!(app.input.as_str(), \"second\");\n1577\t        let _ = app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Up, KeyModifiers::NONE));\n1578\t        assert_eq!(app.input.as_str(), \"first\");\n1579\t        let _ = app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Down, KeyModifiers::NONE));\n1580\t        assert_eq!(app.input.as_str(), \"second\");\n1581\t    }\n1582\t\n1583\t    #[test]\n1584\t    fn enter_submits_but_shift_enter_inserts_newline() {\n1585\t        let mut app = AppState::default();\n1586\t        app.input.set_text(\"line one\".to_string());\n1587\t        let _ = app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Enter, KeyModifiers::SHIFT));\n1588\t        app.input.insert_str(\"line two\");\n1589\t\n1590\t        let action = app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Enter, KeyModifiers::NONE));\n1591\t        match action {\n1592\t            AppAction::Submit(payload) => assert_eq!(payload, \"line one\\nline two\"),\n1593\t            _ => panic!(\"expected submit action\"),\n1594\t        }\n1595\t    }\n1596\t\n1597\t    #[test]\n1598\t    fn ime_preedit_and_commit_do_not_submit_prematurely() {\n1599\t        let mut app = AppState::default();\n1600\t        app.ime_preedit_for_test(\"ni\".to_string());\n1601\t        assert!(matches!(\n1602\t            app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Enter, KeyModifiers::NONE)),\n1603\t            AppAction::None\n1604\t        ));\n1605\t\n1606\t        app.ime_commit_for_test(\"你\".to_string());\n1607\t        assert!(matches!(\n1608\t            app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Enter, KeyModifiers::NONE)),\n1609\t            AppAction::None\n1610\t        ));\n1611\t        assert!(matches!(\n1612\t            app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Enter, KeyModifiers::NONE)),\n1613\t            AppAction::Submit(_)\n1614\t        ));\n1615\t    }\n1616\t\n1617\t    #[test]\n1618\t    fn input_cursor_position_accounts_for_fullwidth_and_wrapping() {\n1619\t        let mut app = AppState::default();\n1620\t        app.input.set_text(\"a你🙂\".to_string());\n1621\t        let pos = app.input_cursor_position(Rect::new(0, 0, 6, 4));\n1622\t        assert_eq!(pos, (2, 2));\n1623\t    }\n1624\t\n1625\t    #[test]\n1626\t    fn key_release_events_are_ignored() {\n1627\t        let mut app = AppState::default();\n1628\t        let key = KeyEvent {\n1629\t            code: KeyCode::Char('x'),\n1630\t            modifiers: KeyModifiers::NONE,\n1631\t            kind: KeyEventKind::Release,\n1632\t            state: KeyEventState::empty(),\n1633\t        };\n1634\t        let action = app.handle_key(key);\n1635\t        assert!(matches!(action, AppAction::None));\n1636\t        assert_eq!(app.input.as_str(), \"\");\n1637\t    }\n1638\t\n1639\t    #[test]\n1640\t    fn error_status_uses_category_label() {\n1641\t        let mut app = AppState::default();\n1642\t        app.push_error_status(\"authentication failed with api key\".to_string());\n1643\t        let rendered = app.render_status();\n1644\t        assert!(rendered.contains(\"[auth]\"));\n1645\t    }\n1646\t\n1647\t    #[test]\n1648\t    fn draw_limiter_throttles_high_frequency_redraws() {\n1649\t        let now = Instant::now();\n1650\t        assert!(!DrawLimiter::should_draw(now));\n1651\t\n1652\t        let old = now - Duration::from_millis(30);\n1653\t        assert!(DrawLimiter::should_draw(old));\n1654\t        assert_eq!(DrawLimiter::next_timeout(old, true), Duration::ZERO);\n1655\t    }\n1656\t\n1657\t    #[test]\n1658\t    fn info_status_category_renders() {\n1659\t        let mut app = AppState::default();\n1660\t        app.push_info_status(\"ready\".to_string());\n1661\t        assert!(matches!(app.status.back().unwrap().kind, StatusKind::Info));\n1662\t    }\n1663\t\n1664\t    #[test]\n1665\t    fn tool_approval_modal_shows_and_denial_is_logged() {\n1666\t        let mut app = AppState::default();\n1667\t        app.open_tool_approval_for_test(\"shell\".to_string(), json!({\"cmd\":\"rm -rf /tmp/demo\"}));\n1668\t\n1669\t        assert!(app.has_pending_tool_approval());\n1670\t        let action = app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Char('n'), KeyModifiers::NONE));\n1671\t        match action {\n1672\t            AppAction::ToolApprovalResolved {\n1673\t                name,\n1674\t                decision: ToolApprovalAction::Deny,\n1675\t            } => assert_eq!(name, \"shell\"),\n1676\t            other => panic!(\"expected deny decision, got {other:?}\"),\n1677\t        }\n1678\t        assert!(!app.has_pending_tool_approval());\n1679\t        let rendered = app.render_conversation();\n1680\t        assert!(\n1681\t            rendered\n1682\t                .iter()\n1683\t                .any(|line| line.to_string().contains(\"[tool:decision] shell deny\")),\n1684\t            \"deny decision should be logged in conversation pane\"\n1685\t        );\n1686\t    }\n1687\t\n1688\t    #[test]\n1689\t    fn tool_approval_modal_supports_tab_and_enter_shortcuts() {\n1690\t        let mut app = AppState::default();\n1691\t        app.open_tool_approval_for_test(\"fs_write\".to_string(), json!({\"path\":\"./a.txt\"}));\n1692\t\n1693\t        let _ = app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Tab, KeyModifiers::NONE));\n1694\t        let action = app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Enter, KeyModifiers::NONE));\n1695\t        assert!(matches!(\n1696\t            action,\n1697\t            AppAction::ToolApprovalResolved {\n1698\t                decision: ToolApprovalAction::Deny,\n1699\t                ..\n1700\t            }\n1701\t        ));\n1702\t    }\n1703\t\n1704\t    #[test]\n1705\t    fn tool_approval_modal_supports_always_allow_shortcut() {\n1706\t        let mut app = AppState::default();\n1707\t        app.open_tool_approval_for_test(\n1708\t            \"browser\".to_string(),\n1709\t            json!({\"url\":\"https://example.com\"}),\n1710\t        );\n1711\t\n1712\t        let action = app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Char('a'), KeyModifiers::NONE));\n1713\t        assert!(matches!(\n1714\t            action,\n1715\t            AppAction::ToolApprovalResolved {\n1716\t                decision: ToolApprovalAction::AllowAlways,\n1717\t                ..\n1718\t            }\n1719\t        ));\n1720\t    }\n1721\t\n1722\t    #[test]\n1723\t    fn worker_panel_tracks_task_details_and_status_badges() {\n1724\t        let mut app = AppState::default();\n1725\t        app.record_worker_event(WorkerUiEvent {\n1726\t            task_id: \"w-1\".to_string(),\n1727\t            status: \"Running\".to_string(),\n1728\t            summary: Some(\"indexing\".to_string()),\n1729\t            timestamp: std::time::UNIX_EPOCH + Duration::from_secs(1),\n1730\t        });\n1731\t        app.record_worker_event(WorkerUiEvent {\n1732\t            task_id: \"w-1\".to_string(),\n1733\t            status: \"Completed\".to_string(),\n1734\t            summary: Some(\"done\".to_string()),\n1735\t            timestamp: std::time::UNIX_EPOCH + Duration::from_secs(3),\n1736\t        });\n1737\t\n1738\t        let selected = app\n1739\t            .selected_worker_task()\n1740\t            .expect(\"selected worker task should exist\");\n1741\t        assert_eq!(selected.task_id, \"w-1\");\n1742\t        assert_eq!(selected.status, \"Completed\");\n1743\t        assert_eq!(selected.summary.as_deref(), Some(\"done\"));\n1744\t        assert_eq!(\n1745\t            selected.started_at,\n1746\t            std::time::UNIX_EPOCH + Duration::from_secs(1)\n1747\t        );\n1748\t        assert_eq!(\n1749\t            selected.updated_at,\n1750\t            std::time::UNIX_EPOCH + Duration::from_secs(3)\n1751\t        );\n1752\t\n1753\t        let panel_lines = app.render_worker_list(20, 80);\n1754\t        assert!(\n1755\t            panel_lines\n1756\t                .iter()\n1757\t                .any(|line| line.to_string().contains(\"[Completed]\")),\n1758\t            \"worker list should render Completed status badge\"\n1759\t        );\n1760\t    }\n1761\t\n1762\t    #[test]\n1763\t    fn worker_panel_selection_and_virtual_scroll_work_for_high_volume() {\n1764\t        let mut app = AppState::default();\n1765\t        for idx in 0..120u64 {\n1766\t            app.record_worker_event(WorkerUiEvent {\n1767\t                task_id: format!(\"w-{idx}\"),\n1768\t                status: \"Running\".to_string(),\n1769\t                summary: Some(format!(\"task {idx}\")),\n1770\t                timestamp: std::time::UNIX_EPOCH + Duration::from_secs(idx),\n1771\t            });\n1772\t        }\n1773\t\n1774\t        for _ in 0..80 {\n1775\t            app.select_next_worker_task();\n1776\t        }\n1777\t\n1778\t        let selected = app\n1779\t            .selected_worker_task()\n1780\t            .expect(\"selected worker task should exist\");\n1781\t        assert_eq!(selected.task_id, \"w-39\");\n1782\t\n1783\t        let lines = app.render_worker_list(10, 80);\n1784\t        assert!(\n1785\t            lines.iter().all(|line| !line.to_string().contains(\"w-119\")),\n1786\t            \"virtual list should not render off-screen task rows\"\n1787\t        );\n1788\t        assert!(\n1789\t            lines.iter().any(|line| line.to_string().contains(\">\")),\n1790\t            \"selected row should be visible and marked\"\n1791\t        );\n1792\t    }\n1793\t}\n1794\t\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b35f4001-d232-4171-b853-fb6a26d102e1","uuid":"db3c7d3c-fc08-4f0a-9e39-dd516d597fa3","timestamp":"2026-04-02T06:24:28.911Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/cli/src/cmd/tui.rs","content":"\nfn spawn_task_stop(\n    bootstrap_state: Arc<BootstrapState>,\n    task_id: String,\n    ui_tx: tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedSender<UiEvent>,\n) {\n    tokio::spawn(async move {\n        let registry = Arc::clone(&bootstrap_state.tool_registry);\n        let tool_ctx = Arc::new(bootstrap_state.tool_ctx());\n        let args = serde_json::json!({\n            \"task_id\": task_id.clone(),\n            \"summary\": \"stopped from tui worker panel\"\n        });\n\n        let _ = ui_tx.send(UiEvent::ToolStart {\n            name: \"task_stop\".to_string(),\n            args: args.clone(),\n        });\n\n        let result = registry\n            .execute(\"task_stop\", args, &tool_ctx)\n            .await\n            .map_err(|err| err.to_string());\n\n        if let Ok(payload) = &result\n            && let Ok(value) = serde_json::from_str::<Value>(payload)\n            && let (Some(task_id), Some(status_raw)) = (\n                value.get(\"task_id\").and_then(Value::as_str),\n                value.get(\"status\").and_then(Value::as_str),\n            )\n            && let Some(status) = worker_status_label(status_raw)\n        {\n            let summary = value\n                .get(\"summary\")\n                .and_then(Value::as_str)\n                .map(ToString::to_string);\n            let _ = ui_tx.send(UiEvent::WorkerStatus {\n                task_id: task_id.to_string(),\n                status: status.to_string(),\n                summary,\n                timestamp: SystemTime::now(),\n            });\n        }\n\n        let _ = ui_tx.send(UiEvent::ToolDone {\n            name: \"task_stop\".to_string(),\n            success: result.is_ok(),\n        });\n\n        if let Err(message) = result {\n            let _ = ui_tx.send(UiEvent::ToolError {\n                name: \"task_stop\".to_string(),\n                message,\n            });\n        }\n    });\n}\n\nstruct TerminalGuard;\n\nimpl Drop for TerminalGuard {\n    fn drop(&mut self) {\n        let _ = restore_terminal();\n    }\n}\n\nfn restore_terminal() -> io::Result<()> {\n    disable_raw_mode()?;\n    execute!(io::stdout(), LeaveAlternateScreen)?;\n    Ok(())\n}\n\nfn install_panic_restoration_hook() {\n    static INIT_HOOK: std::sync::Once = std::sync::Once::new();\n\n    INIT_HOOK.call_once(|| {\n        let original = std::panic::take_hook();\n        std::panic::set_hook(Box::new(move |panic_info| {\n            let _ = restore_terminal();\n            original(panic_info);\n        }));\n    });\n}\n\n#[cfg(test)]\nmod tests {\n    use super::{\n        AppAction, AppState, ConversationLine, DrawLimiter, StatusKind, ToolApprovalAction,\n        WorkerUiEvent, split_layout,\n    };\n    use crossterm::event::{KeyCode, KeyEvent, KeyEventKind, KeyEventState, KeyModifiers};\n    use ratatui::layout::Rect;\n    use serde_json::json;\n    use std::time::{Duration, Instant};\n\n    #[test]\n    fn splits_into_four_panes() {\n        let [conversation, worker, status, input] = split_layout(Rect::new(0, 0, 120, 40));\n\n        assert_eq!(conversation.width + worker.width, 120);\n        assert_eq!(status.height, 5);\n        assert_eq!(input.height, 3);\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn ctrl_c_quits() {\n        let mut app = AppState::default();\n\n        let action = app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Char('c'), KeyModifiers::CONTROL));\n\n        assert!(matches!(action, AppAction::Quit));\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn appends_deltas_to_active_assistant_message() {\n        let mut app = AppState::default();\n        app.apply_delta(\"hello\");\n        app.apply_delta(\" world\");\n        app.close_active_assistant();\n        app.apply_delta(\"new\");\n\n        assert_eq!(app.conversation.len(), 2);\n        match &app.conversation[0] {\n            ConversationLine::Assistant(content) => assert_eq!(content, \"hello world\"),\n            other => panic!(\"unexpected conversation entry: {other:?}\"),\n        }\n        match &app.conversation[1] {\n            ConversationLine::Assistant(content) => assert_eq!(content, \"new\"),\n            other => panic!(\"unexpected conversation entry: {other:?}\"),\n        }\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn tool_timeline_marks_success_and_failure() {\n        let mut app = AppState::default();\n        app.push_tool_done(\"shell\".to_string(), true);\n        app.push_tool_done(\"shell\".to_string(), false);\n\n        let lines = app.render_conversation();\n        assert!(lines.iter().any(|l| l.to_string().contains(\"[ok]\")));\n        assert!(lines.iter().any(|l| l.to_string().contains(\"[fail]\")));\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn conversation_scroll_navigation_changes_offset() {\n        let mut app = AppState::default();\n        app.conversation_scroll = 10;\n        let _ = app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Up, KeyModifiers::CONTROL));\n        assert_eq!(app.conversation_scroll, 9);\n        let _ = app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::PageDown, KeyModifiers::NONE));\n        assert_eq!(app.conversation_scroll, 19);\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn grapheme_aware_backspace_and_cursor_navigation() {\n        let mut app = AppState::default();\n        let _ = app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Char('a'), KeyModifiers::NONE));\n        let _ = app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Char('🙂'), KeyModifiers::NONE));\n        let _ = app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Char('你'), KeyModifiers::NONE));\n\n        let _ = app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Left, KeyModifiers::NONE));\n        let _ = app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Backspace, KeyModifiers::NONE));\n\n        assert_eq!(app.input.as_str(), \"a你\");\n        let _ = app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Right, KeyModifiers::NONE));\n        assert_eq!(app.input.as_str(), \"a你\");\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn up_down_recalls_input_history() {\n        let mut app = AppState::default();\n        app.input.set_text(\"first\".to_string());\n        assert!(matches!(app.submit_input(), AppAction::Submit(_)));\n        app.input.set_text(\"second\".to_string());\n        assert!(matches!(app.submit_input(), AppAction::Submit(_)));\n\n        let _ = app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Up, KeyModifiers::NONE));\n        assert_eq!(app.input.as_str(), \"second\");\n        let _ = app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Up, KeyModifiers::NONE));\n        assert_eq!(app.input.as_str(), \"first\");\n        let _ = app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Down, KeyModifiers::NONE));\n        assert_eq!(app.input.as_str(), \"second\");\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn enter_submits_but_shift_enter_inserts_newline() {\n        let mut app = AppState::default();\n        app.input.set_text(\"line one\".to_string());\n        let _ = app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Enter, KeyModifiers::SHIFT));\n        app.input.insert_str(\"line two\");\n\n        let action = app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Enter, KeyModifiers::NONE));\n        match action {\n            AppAction::Submit(payload) => assert_eq!(payload, \"line one\\nline two\"),\n            _ => panic!(\"expected submit action\"),\n        }\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn ime_preedit_and_commit_do_not_submit_prematurely() {\n        let mut app = AppState::default();\n        app.ime_preedit_for_test(\"ni\".to_string());\n        assert!(matches!(\n            app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Enter, KeyModifiers::NONE)),\n            AppAction::None\n        ));\n\n        app.ime_commit_for_test(\"你\".to_string());\n        assert!(matches!(\n            app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Enter, KeyModifiers::NONE)),\n            AppAction::None\n        ));\n        assert!(matches!(\n            app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Enter, KeyModifiers::NONE)),\n            AppAction::Submit(_)\n        ));\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn input_cursor_position_accounts_for_fullwidth_and_wrapping() {\n        let mut app = AppState::default();\n        app.input.set_text(\"a你🙂\".to_string());\n        let pos = app.input_cursor_position(Rect::new(0, 0, 6, 4));\n        assert_eq!(pos, (2, 2));\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn key_release_events_are_ignored() {\n        let mut app = AppState::default();\n        let key = KeyEvent {\n            code: KeyCode::Char('x'),\n            modifiers: KeyModifiers::NONE,\n            kind: KeyEventKind::Release,\n            state: KeyEventState::empty(),\n        };\n        let action = app.handle_key(key);\n        assert!(matches!(action, AppAction::None));\n        assert_eq!(app.input.as_str(), \"\");\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn error_status_uses_category_label() {\n        let mut app = AppState::default();\n        app.push_error_status(\"authentication failed with api key\".to_string());\n        let rendered = app.render_status();\n        assert!(rendered.contains(\"[auth]\"));\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn draw_limiter_throttles_high_frequency_redraws() {\n        let now = Instant::now();\n        assert!(!DrawLimiter::should_draw(now));\n\n        let old = now - Duration::from_millis(30);\n        assert!(DrawLimiter::should_draw(old));\n        assert_eq!(DrawLimiter::next_timeout(old, true), Duration::ZERO);\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn info_status_category_renders() {\n        let mut app = AppState::default();\n        app.push_info_status(\"ready\".to_string());\n        assert!(matches!(app.status.back().unwrap().kind, StatusKind::Info));\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn tool_approval_modal_shows_and_denial_is_logged() {\n        let mut app = AppState::default();\n        app.open_tool_approval_for_test(\"shell\".to_string(), json!({\"cmd\":\"rm -rf /tmp/demo\"}));\n\n        assert!(app.has_pending_tool_approval());\n        let action = app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Char('n'), KeyModifiers::NONE));\n        match action {\n            AppAction::ToolApprovalResolved {\n                name,\n                decision: ToolApprovalAction::Deny,\n            } => assert_eq!(name, \"shell\"),\n            other => panic!(\"expected deny decision, got {other:?}\"),\n        }\n        assert!(!app.has_pending_tool_approval());\n        let rendered = app.render_conversation();\n        assert!(\n            rendered\n                .iter()\n                .any(|line| line.to_string().contains(\"[tool:decision] shell deny\")),\n            \"deny decision should be logged in conversation pane\"\n        );\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn tool_approval_modal_supports_tab_and_enter_shortcuts() {\n        let mut app = AppState::default();\n        app.open_tool_approval_for_test(\"fs_write\".to_string(), json!({\"path\":\"./a.txt\"}));\n\n        let _ = app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Tab, KeyModifiers::NONE));\n        let action = app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Enter, KeyModifiers::NONE));\n        assert!(matches!(\n            action,\n            AppAction::ToolApprovalResolved {\n                decision: ToolApprovalAction::Deny,\n                ..\n            }\n        ));\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn tool_approval_modal_supports_always_allow_shortcut() {\n        let mut app = AppState::default();\n        app.open_tool_approval_for_test(\n            \"browser\".to_string(),\n            json!({\"url\":\"https://example.com\"}),\n        );\n\n        let action = app.handle_key(KeyEvent::new(KeyCode::Char('a'), KeyModifiers::NONE));\n        assert!(matches!(\n            action,\n            AppAction::ToolApprovalResolved {\n                decision: ToolApprovalAction::AllowAlways,\n                ..\n            }\n        ));\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn worker_panel_tracks_task_details_and_status_badges() {\n        let mut app = AppState::default();\n        app.record_worker_event(WorkerUiEvent {\n            task_id: \"w-1\".to_string(),\n            status: \"Running\".to_string(),\n            summary: Some(\"indexing\".to_string()),\n            timestamp: std::time::UNIX_EPOCH + Duration::from_secs(1),\n        });\n        app.record_worker_event(WorkerUiEvent {\n            task_id: \"w-1\".to_string(),\n            status: \"Completed\".to_string(),\n            summary: Some(\"done\".to_string()),\n            timestamp: std::time::UNIX_EPOCH + Duration::from_secs(3),\n        });\n\n        let selected = app\n            .selected_worker_task()\n            .expect(\"selected worker task should exist\");\n        assert_eq!(selected.task_id, \"w-1\");\n        assert_eq!(selected.status, \"Completed\");\n        assert_eq!(selected.summary.as_deref(), Some(\"done\"));\n        assert_eq!(\n            selected.started_at,\n            std::time::UNIX_EPOCH + Duration::from_secs(1)\n        );\n        assert_eq!(\n            selected.updated_at,\n            std::time::UNIX_EPOCH + Duration::from_secs(3)\n        );\n\n        let panel_lines = app.render_worker_list(20, 80);\n        assert!(\n            panel_lines\n                .iter()\n                .any(|line| line.to_string().contains(\"[Completed]\")),\n            \"worker list should render Completed status badge\"\n        );\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn worker_panel_selection_and_virtual_scroll_work_for_high_volume() {\n        let mut app = AppState::default();\n        for idx in 0..120u64 {\n            app.record_worker_event(WorkerUiEvent {\n                task_id: format!(\"w-{idx}\"),\n                status: \"Running\".to_string(),\n                summary: Some(format!(\"task {idx}\")),\n                timestamp: std::time::UNIX_EPOCH + Duration::from_secs(idx),\n            });\n        }\n\n        for _ in 0..80 {\n            app.select_next_worker_task();\n        }\n\n        let selected = app\n            .selected_worker_task()\n            .expect(\"selected worker task should exist\");\n        assert_eq!(selected.task_id, \"w-39\");\n\n        let lines = app.render_worker_list(10, 80);\n        assert!(\n            lines.iter().all(|line| !line.to_string().contains(\"w-119\")),\n            \"virtual list should not render off-screen task rows\"\n        );\n        assert!(\n            lines.iter().any(|line| line.to_string().contains(\">\")),\n            \"selected row should be visible and marked\"\n        );\n    }\n}\n","numLines":396,"startLine":1399,"totalLines":1794}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01WnUAJaZ9FwrPjwaUexHcCc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the codebase. Let me plan the implementation for US-034:\n\n## Acceptance Criteria Analysis:\n\n1. **Provide default and high-contrast color themes configurable in settings** - Need to add theme config to `Config` in schema.rs, and implement a `Theme` struct with color/style definitions in tui.rs\n\n2. **Respect no-color / limited-color terminals with sane fallbacks** - Need to detect `NO_COLOR` env var, `TERM=dumb`, and fall back to monochrome styles\n\n3. **All key actions have visible hints and non-color status indicators** - Status panel and worker panel need non-color status indicators (already has `[info]`, `[auth]`, etc. \n\nI can enhance these with additional markers like `[!]` for errors and `[*]` for info to make them more distinctive.\n\n4. **Terminal capability check falls back to standard REPL when unsupported** - Need to detect if terminal supports alternate screen/raw mode and fall back to simple REPL if not\n\n5. **Startup and teardown leave terminal in clean state after crashes (best-effort)** - Already has TerminalGuard and panic hook, but may need improvement\n\n6. **cargo fmt --check passes** - Format\n\n7. **cargo clippy --workspace -- -D warnings passes** - Clean\n\n8. **cargo test --workspace passes** - Tests pass\n\n## Implementation Plan:\n\n### 1. Add theme configuration...\n\n### 2. Creating a Theme module...\n\n### 3. Terminal capability detection...\n\n### 4. REPL fallback mode...\n\n### 5. Enhancing status display...\n\nThe key insight here is that the existing text markers like `[ok]`, `[fail]`, `[info]`, `[auth]` already provide accessibility without color, so I just need to layer color styles on top via a `Theme` struct, add detection for `NO_COLOR` and `TERM=dumb`, implement a basic REPL fallback when the terminal can't support raw mode, and improve panic cleanup. Let me examine what the current implementation looks like to see where these pieces fit.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5659,"cache_read_input_tokens":44318,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5659},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b35f4001-d232-4171-b853-fb6a26d102e1","uuid":"37512b5f-3901-454b-9024-52e60f9f4427"}
