 tokio::task::spawn_blocking(move || -> anyhow::Result<()> {\n        let mut editor = DefaultEditor::new()?;\n        // Persists across all turns within this REPL session\n        let always_allowed: Arc<Mutex<HashSet<String>>> = Arc::new(Mutex::new(HashSet::new()));\n        let formatter: Arc<Mutex<StreamFormatter>> = Arc::new(Mutex::new(StreamFormatter::new()));\n        // Persona is applied only on the first turn (new session); subsequent turns pass None\n        let mut persona_once: Option<String> = persona;\n\n        loop {\n            match editor.readline(\"You: \") {\n                Ok(line) => {\n                    let input = line.trim().to_string();\n                    if input.is_empty() {\n                        continue;\n                    }\n                    if input == \"exit\" || input == \"quit\" {\n                        break;","numLines":80,"startLine":1,"totalLines":201}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01MEFAWvNvmgfeUfugH1nrfF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the codebase. Let me implement US-034.\n\nThe key things to implement:\n\n1. **Theme struct** in tui.rs with three themes: Default, HighContrast, NoColor\n2. **Terminal capability detection**: NO_COLOR env var, TERM=dumb, color depth\n3. **Fallback to REPL** when terminal doesn't support raw mode\n4. **Apply themed styles** across all widgets\n5. **Config changes** in schema.rs\n6. **Tests** for theme detection and fallback behavior\n\nLet me think carefully about the implementation:\n\n### Theme Design\n\n\nI'm defining the theme structure with an enum for the three theme variants and a struct that holds all the style configurations for different UI elements like panels, conversation messages, status indicators, and worker states.\n\nNow I'm thinking through the color assignments for each theme—the default theme uses ratatui's color palette with cyan and blue for user messages, green for assistant responses, and yellow/green/red for tool outcomes, while the high-contrast theme relies on bold and underline modifiers for accessibility, and the no-color theme strips all colors entirely to respect the NO_COLOR environment variable or dumb terminals.\n\nI'm also starting to implement the color support detection logic that checks for the NO_COLOR environment variable first, then examines the TERM variable to determine what color capabilities are available.\n\nDetecting terminal color support...\n\nFor the REPL fallback, I need to ensure that when raw mode isn't available or when we're in a dumb terminal with no color support, the system gracefully falls back to the standard REPL interface instead of trying to render the fancy UI. if enable_raw_mode() fails or if TERM=dumb, we should fall back to the existing REPL (repl.rs).\n\nLet me think about how to do this cleanly. The `run_ui_loop` function currently calls `enable_raw_mode()` which returns an error. We can catch this error and call the repl instead. But the TUI function doesn't have access to ReplArgs...\n\nActually, looking at the main.rs to understand how TUI is invoked. Looking at the existing architecture, the fallback should be:\n1. Try to detect if raw mode is supported  \n2. If not, print a warning and fall back to basic text output\n\nActually for the fallback to REPL, I think the simplest approach is:\n- In `run()` (the entry point), detect terminal capabilities\n- If unsupported, return a special error or just run a basic loop\n\nLet me look at how the tui `run` function is called from main.rs. I need to understand the entry point to wire this up properly.\n\nThe acceptance criteria says \"falls back to standard REPL when unsupported\", which means I should call the repl run function when raw mode fails. I'd need to construct a default ReplArgs with session, persona, and no_confirm all set to their defaults, then invoke `repl::run()` from the TUI entry point if raw mode isn't available.\n\nLet me check main.rs to see how everything connects.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3628,"cache_read_input_tokens":49977,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3628},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b35f4001-d232-4171-b853-fb6a26d102e1","uuid":"f38d35a1-66df-47b6-a742-8e0e985592b6"}
